02:13.288 --> 02:15.940
These spring rolls are amazing.

02:15.942 --> 02:17.158
Good job, Bernadette.

02:17.160 --> 02:20.294
That's the takeout
that Sheldon brought.

02:22.364 --> 02:25.166
Oh, well, I'm sure
they wouldn't have tasted

02:25.168 --> 02:27.818
nearly as good if I hadn't tried
your food first.

02:31.690 --> 02:34.542
Howard, did you want
your clothes arranged

02:34.544 --> 02:36.327
seasonally or by color?

02:36.329 --> 02:37.462
Color's fine.

02:37.464 --> 02:39.430
Wrong, they'll be
arranged seasonally.

02:41.016 --> 02:43.217
Sheldon, aren't you gonna spend
a little time with Amy?

02:43.219 --> 02:44.685
Oh, it's okay, I'm used to it.

02:44.687 --> 02:46.837
The other day at Whole Foods,
he spent an hour

02:46.839 --> 02:49.307
optimizing the cheese aisle.

02:49.309 --> 02:50.525
Yeah, and some thanks I got.

02:50.527 --> 02:52.343
The assistant manager
chased me out

02:52.345 --> 02:54.345
with an artisanal salami.

02:55.647 --> 02:58.849
His quirks
just make you love him more.

03:00.536 --> 03:02.520
Someone please agree with me.

03:08.076 --> 03:09.127
Sheldon, come on.

03:09.129 --> 03:10.461
It's getting late.
Time to go.

03:10.463 --> 03:13.381
Oh, five more minutes.

03:13.383 --> 03:15.416
That's what you said
five minutes ago.

03:15.418 --> 03:17.135
Amy and Penny
are already in the car.

03:17.137 --> 03:18.252
Let's move it.

03:18.254 --> 03:21.672
How come I never get to do
anything I want to do?

03:21.674 --> 03:23.641
You know, if he really wants
to stay and finish,

03:23.643 --> 03:25.042
I can give him
a ride home.

03:25.044 --> 03:28.095
Please, Leonard!
He said it's okay!

03:28.097 --> 03:29.147
Sheldon, it's--

03:29.149 --> 03:31.549
Wait, I can go home
without you? Bye!

03:33.602 --> 03:36.270
Howard, I have
a few questions.

03:36.272 --> 03:38.906
I found three
bowling pins.

03:38.908 --> 03:43.394
Now, do you juggle these,
or are you missing seven?

03:43.396 --> 03:44.745
Juggle.

03:44.747 --> 03:46.697
You health nuts kill me.

03:50.903 --> 03:53.621
Oh, my God,
it's beautiful!

03:53.623 --> 03:56.457
Look, he found the
juggling pins I hid.

03:56.459 --> 03:58.593
Uh, just a couple
more items.

03:58.595 --> 04:01.012
Howard, I found this letter
from your dad in a box.

04:01.014 --> 04:02.296
Now, based on
the content,

04:02.298 --> 04:04.248
it could either be filed...

04:04.250 --> 04:05.766
Whoa, you opened this?

04:05.768 --> 04:07.718
Well, I had to find out if
it was personal correspondence

04:07.720 --> 04:09.587
or memorabilia.
Now, as I was saying,

04:09.589 --> 04:11.922
based on the content...
I couldn't be less interested.

04:13.826 --> 04:16.360
Now, come on,
I'll take you home.

04:16.362 --> 04:18.029
Howard, don't you want to
know what's in the letter?

04:18.031 --> 04:20.231
If I wanted to know,
I would've opened it years ago.

04:21.099 --> 04:22.984
The closet looks great.

04:22.986 --> 04:24.318
Let's get out of here.

04:24.320 --> 04:25.953
Wait, can I
bring this box

04:25.955 --> 04:28.573
of extra shirt buttons
to sort on the ride?

04:28.575 --> 04:31.492
Do whatever you want.

04:31.494 --> 04:32.943
Thanks.

04:33.745 --> 04:34.745
Oh.

04:34.747 --> 04:36.297
Great party.

04:40.719 --> 04:42.169
You know, when I
first met Howard,

04:42.171 --> 04:44.171
he would pull his scrotum
out of his shorts

04:44.173 --> 04:46.457
and say, "Oh,
I sat in gum."

04:51.563 --> 04:53.548
What is your point?

04:53.550 --> 04:55.850
Well, it's just kind of weird
how grown up he is now.

04:55.852 --> 04:58.069
Happily married guy
throwing dinner parties.

04:58.071 --> 04:59.654
Really? You couldn't
just say that?

04:59.656 --> 05:01.856
You had to tell
the scrotum story?

05:03.775 --> 05:06.277
Trying to paint a picture.

05:07.112 --> 05:09.497
Yeah, it was
a nice change of pace

05:09.499 --> 05:11.482
not eating takeout
around a coffee table.

05:11.484 --> 05:14.151
Mm, you know, we could
throw a dinner party, too.

05:14.153 --> 05:16.254
Maybe even ask everyone
to get dressed up.

05:16.256 --> 05:17.204
Sure.

05:17.206 --> 05:18.706
Just, when you say
"dressed up,"

05:18.708 --> 05:19.990
you mean
nice clothes, right?

05:19.992 --> 05:21.876
Not, like, capes
and tights and crap?

05:23.679 --> 05:25.596
Yeah.

05:25.598 --> 05:26.764
Although...

05:26.766 --> 05:28.299
No!

05:34.673 --> 05:36.173
Howie, you okay?

05:36.175 --> 05:39.393
Yeah, I just...
couldn't sleep.

05:39.395 --> 05:41.646
Told you you shouldn't
have espresso after dinner.

05:41.648 --> 05:44.098
I know the little cups
make you feel big,

05:44.100 --> 05:46.651
but it's not worth it.

05:48.570 --> 05:50.071
It's this stupid letter.

05:50.073 --> 05:51.489
Did you read it?

05:51.491 --> 05:53.040
No.

05:53.042 --> 05:54.792
You must be curious.

05:54.794 --> 05:56.210
Of course I'm curious.

05:56.212 --> 05:58.663
I haven't seen
the man since,

05:58.665 --> 06:00.748
oh, I was a little kid.

06:00.750 --> 06:03.584
And a letter shows up
on my 18th birthday?

06:03.586 --> 06:05.386
What's that about?

06:05.388 --> 06:06.870
Why don't you read it?

06:06.872 --> 06:10.057
Maybe he apologizes or
explains why he left.

06:10.059 --> 06:12.009
He abandoned
me and my mother.

06:12.011 --> 06:16.880
Why does he deserve
a chance to explain anything?

06:16.882 --> 06:19.016
I get that.

06:19.018 --> 06:21.402
So, what do you
want to do with it?

06:21.404 --> 06:24.772
Something I should've done
a long time ago.

06:27.576 --> 06:29.276
Really? Are you sure?

06:29.278 --> 06:31.495
Yep.

06:38.788 --> 06:40.121
Feel better?

06:40.123 --> 06:41.922
I do.

06:45.777 --> 06:46.927
Great.

06:46.929 --> 06:50.247
Neither one of us is
tall enough to reach that.

06:55.887 --> 06:58.639
I can't believe
he set it on fire.

06:58.641 --> 07:01.475
Yeah, just seeing that letter
really freaked him out.

07:01.477 --> 07:03.527
And he was already
having a tough day

07:03.529 --> 07:06.697
'cause he accidentally wore
my pants to work.

07:11.203 --> 07:12.870
I don't know why <i>he</i> was upset.

07:12.872 --> 07:15.272
They were bigger on him than me.

07:17.542 --> 07:19.193
Boy, I'm really curious
what's in that letter.

07:19.195 --> 07:21.579
Me, too, but I guess
now we'll never know.

07:21.581 --> 07:22.913
Well, you said Sheldon read it.

07:22.915 --> 07:24.048
Why not ask him?

07:24.050 --> 07:25.082
I can't do that.

07:25.084 --> 07:26.550
What kind of wife would I be

07:26.552 --> 07:28.252
if I didn't respect
my husband's privacy?

07:28.254 --> 07:29.286
What if I ask Sheldon,

07:29.288 --> 07:30.755
you just happen to be
in the room?

07:30.757 --> 07:32.640
That works.
Okay.

